<h2 id="revisiting">Revisiting</h2>

<p>After two years, I am finally updating some studies I have done.</p>

<hr />

<h3 id="thing-that-resists">Thing that resists</h3>

<p>Here I will post on my exploration of hand made component - resistor. Starting from the question “could I use anything if the material resist?” Resistor provides presise amount of resistance to the circuit, controlling the flow. As the word “resistor” describe, things that resist.</p>

<h3 id="symbols-and-material">Symbols and Material</h3>

<p>As I am working with the design of circuits for each bugs, these elemental materials becomes symbols. Symbols that represent the material quality. This abstraction allow me to focus and conceptualise the relationships made in a particular scale. Material dissapears and just shapes are left - to be able to see the entire forest.</p>

<p>But there is always a gap between symbols and materials. Idea and actuality. Recepes and cooked meal. Words and feelings. There is a song by a band called くるり quruli that is “言葉はさんかく　こころは四角” which translates to “words are triangle, feelings are square” there will always be a gap. There is something about working with circuits, (maybe partly because my lack in depth in technical knowledge) it is a process of seeing this difference between preceved idea and materiality. It reminds me that there is always unknown left lerking. Infinite grainy variables that can’t be captured. Platonic ιδέα、idea can not exist. We are just left with the noise. The gap.</p>

